oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Island Home
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: unknown
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Island Home, Perez Dickinson home and farm. Caption by Mrs. Fayette Van Deventer. The sluice which separated the island farm from the mainland of "Island Home" farm which all belonged to Col. Perez Dickinson. This picture looks north, up the Tennessee River. Taken about 1887.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Rivers; Sluices;
